{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/child-maltreatment-recognition-management/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"548a82c5-7402-5e85-8db2-e82a694f3358","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 09d7707c-dc0f-4f89-9314-3e56fa0b1426 --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 09d7707c-dc0f-4f89-9314-3e56fa0b1426 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item faa5679b-3de8-44d3-aa60-68c56bb859bd --><!-- begin field d1ec7f26-75e2-4344-b4bf-404fdbdf0c29 --><ul><li><strong>The actual prevalence of child maltreatment is unknown</strong> as it is recognized that a large proportion of affected children are not known to child protection services and police-recorded crime statistics do not necessarily reflect the actual number of offences committed.</li><li><strong>Children/young people of all ages can be affected, but the highest recorded incidence is in babies and toddlers.</strong></li><li><strong>Around 80% of child abuse is perpetrated by carers or parents.</strong></li><li><strong>A 2018 National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Children report published the annual UK police-recorded number of child maltreatment offences, which included:</strong><ul><li><strong>Cruelty and neglect </strong>— 15,204.</li><li><strong>Sexual offences against children </strong>(including rape, sexual assault, grooming, and offences relating to indecent images of children) — 52,339.</li><li><strong>Indecent communication with a child</strong> (including online) — 3,640.</li><li><strong>Deaths of children under the age of 15 as a result of assault or undetermined intent</strong> — 58.</li><li><strong>Child homicides</strong> (including murder, manslaughter and infanticide) — 98.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Self-reported data indicate that almost 1 in every 5 young people aged 11-17 consider themselves to have experienced high levels of abuse or neglect and almost 1 in every 20 have experienced 'contact' sexual abuse.</strong></li><li><strong>There were 58,533 children in the UK subject to child protection plans (that is, considered to be at risk of harm) for the year ending on 31 March 2017. </strong>In England the most common reason for a child protection plan was neglect, followed by emotional, physical, then sexual abuse.<ul><li>There were 66,380 looked-after children, placed in care due to maltreatment for the year ending 31 March 2017.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/child-maltreatment-recognition-management/references/\">BMJ Best Practice, 2018</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/child-maltreatment-recognition-management/references/\">NSPCC, 2018b</a>]</p><!-- end field d1ec7f26-75e2-4344-b4bf-404fdbdf0c29 --><!-- end item faa5679b-3de8-44d3-aa60-68c56bb859bd -->","topic":{"id":"399c706c-d925-5357-8bd0-fb82cd95ee01","topicId":"7e199db4-11c4-42e5-8f2d-878014e6b1ee","topicName":"Child maltreatment - recognition and management","slug":"child-maltreatment-recognition-management","lastRevised":"Last revised in January 2019","chapters":[{"id":"44455b04-f8f9-5618-936e-0f3ee64eff15","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"adf16a06-53ba-50f6-b77c-723ecd9b3220","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d5b2b953-c8cc-5be0-b514-38c4c95eca62","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"727476e5-0ff0-56a5-a9b2-7dc9ce1c5de4","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"7d13d77e-1923-5987-b363-d99c2e6646bb","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"d65e5f53-9b67-5099-ae1a-7ed5f26cc490","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"fb949766-5f45-5bbd-bacd-cabd51c7a0c5","slug":"goals","f